result.execSummary:
The defendant Dakota D.S. Piper was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Escape-Criminal Arrest, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.42(3)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Concurrent to Count 2.  Consecutive to any other sentence.

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

superMiscConds.notes: If Extended Supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
Undertake AODA assessment and comply with treatment recommendations.

Defendant shall Maintain Absolute Sobriety.  No use or possession of controlled substances, unless prescribed by a physician.   No possession of drug paraphernalia.  No possession or consumption of intoxicants.

Complete compas assessment,  counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate and followup.  Pay supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections and follow rules of supervision.  Defendant shall provide a DNA sample to Winnebago County Jail immediately upon request.  

NO CONTACT WITH : Brandon Kielcheski, Christian Palomar, Courtney Becher, Tyler Klemetsen, Svetla Ionova, Anna Koeppel.
